cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about RGBT tracking, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel deep fusion algorithm based on an end-to-end trained convolutional neural network, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of pruning techniques to remove redundant and noisy features, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with multi-modal data, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper's application in tracking objects can be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
